From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Lusoris <lusoris@pm.me>
Date: Mon, 15 Jun 2026 11:40:20 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 5/7] feat(qsv): honor AV_FRAME_DATA_REGIONS_OF_INTEREST via
 the per-block QP map
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Stock qsvenc.c already maps ROI side data onto mfxExtEncoderROI (rectangle
regions, capped at QSV_MAX_ROI_NUM and at rectangle granularity). This adds a
`pelorus_roi` AVOption (default off) that instead rasterizes each
AVRegionOfInterest's qoffset into Intel QSV's *dense* per-block delta-QP map
(mfxExtMBQP, Mode = MFX_MBQP_MODE_QP_DELTA, attached per frame via the existing
mfxEncodeCtrl ext-buffer chain; mfxExtCodingOption3::EnableMBQP turned on at
init), mirroring the merged NVENC qpDeltaMap patch (ADR-0114 Tier 1).

Dense map vs region rectangles: the vf_pelorus_analyze banding map is per-cell;
coalescing it into <=256 rectangles loses fidelity, whereas mfxExtMBQP carries a
per-16x16-block delta directly with no rectangle budget — same value path as the
NVENC delta-QP map it mirrors. qoffset->delta uses the libx264 convention
(qp_range = 51 + 6*(depth-8)); region precedence + self_size stride mirror
libx264's setup_roi.

Portable by construction (this ships to all users, not the dev box):
- block size is the SDK-documented 16x16 MBQP alignment for both AVC and HEVC
  (mfxExtMBQP), not any one GPU's coding-tree size; HEVC also carries BlockSize.
- runtime capability probe: EnableMBQP is only honored under CQP rate control
  (mfxExtCodingOption3 doc), so non-CQP sessions emit one warning and pass
  through unchanged; the whole path is compile-guarded by QSV_HAVE_MBQP
  (oneVPL / MediaSDK API >= 1.13) so older SDK headers no-op cleanly.
- no device-node / driver / entrypoint assumptions; zero behaviour change when
  the option is off (default).

Lets Pelorus's measured banding-ROI (vf_pelorus_analyze roi=1, ADR-0114 Tier 0)
steer Intel-hardware bit allocation through the same standard ROI side data the
merged analyze filter already emits — no new producer.

Verified: cc -fsyntax-only of the changed libavcodec TUs against the installed
oneVPL headers; full-stack regeneration applies cleanly. Full QSV ffmpeg rebuild
and on-Arc BD-rate proof are a follow-up (no fabricated numbers).
---
 libavcodec/qsvenc.c      | 175 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++-
 libavcodec/qsvenc.h      |  18 ++++
 libavcodec/qsvenc_h264.c |   2 +
 libavcodec/qsvenc_hevc.c |   2 +
 4 files changed, 196 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/libavcodec/qsvenc.c b/libavcodec/qsvenc.c
index fc1b8795d8..83cd732250 100644
--- a/libavcodec/qsvenc.c
+++ b/libavcodec/qsvenc.c
@@ -1113,6 +1113,36 @@ static int init_video_param(AVCodecContext *avctx, QSVEncContext *q)
         q->extco3.Header.BufferId      = MFX_EXTBUFF_CODING_OPTION3;
         q->extco3.Header.BufferSz      = sizeof(q->extco3);
 
+#if QSV_HAVE_MBQP
+        /* Pelorus: per-block QP steering requires EnableMBQP at init, and the
+         * SDK only honors it under CQP rate control (mfxExtCodingOption3 doc).
+         * Probe that here and degrade gracefully: if the precondition fails we
+         * clear pelorus_roi so the per-frame path becomes a pass-through. */
+        if (q->pelorus_roi &&
+            (avctx->codec_id == AV_CODEC_ID_HEVC ||
+             avctx->codec_id == AV_CODEC_ID_H264)) {
+            if (q->param.mfx.RateControlMethod == MFX_RATECONTROL_CQP) {
+                q->extco3.EnableMBQP = MFX_CODINGOPTION_ON;
+                av_log(avctx, AV_LOG_VERBOSE,
+                       "Pelorus ROI: per-block delta-QP map (mfxExtMBQP) enabled.\n");
+            } else {
+                av_log(avctx, AV_LOG_WARNING,
+                       "pelorus_roi requires CQP rate control for the per-block "
+                       "QP map; disabling ROI steering.\n");
+                q->pelorus_roi = 0;
+            }
+        }
+#else
+        if (q->pelorus_roi) {
+            av_log(avctx, AV_LOG_WARNING,
+                   "pelorus_roi requested but mfxExtMBQP is unavailable "
+                   "(oneVPL/MediaSDK API 1.13 or greater required at compile "
+                   "time); ignoring.
+");
+            q->pelorus_roi = 0;
+        }
+#endif
+
         if (avctx->codec_id == AV_CODEC_ID_HEVC ||
             avctx->codec_id == AV_CODEC_ID_H264) {
             switch (q->p_strategy) {
@@ -2129,6 +2159,132 @@ static void print_interlace_msg(AVCodecContext *avctx, QSVEncContext *q)
     }
 }
 
+#if QSV_HAVE_MBQP
+/* Pelorus: size in luma pixels of one mfxExtMBQP DeltaQP entry. The oneVPL /
+ * MediaSDK docs fix the MBQP map at a 16x16 block alignment for *both* AVC and
+ * HEVC ("MBQP map should be aligned for 16x16 block size", mfxExtMBQP), so the
+ * array layout is 16x16 regardless of codec. (HEVC additionally exposes the
+ * BlockSize field; 16 is always a legal value and keeps the rasterizer codec-
+ * independent -- we do not assume any one GPU's coding-tree size.) */
+#define PELORUS_QSV_MBQP_BLOCK 16
+
+/* Pelorus: build a per-block delta-QP map from AV_FRAME_DATA_REGIONS_OF_INTEREST
+ * and attach it to the per-frame mfxEncodeCtrl as an mfxExtMBQP ext-buffer.
+ * Mirrors libavcodec/libx264.c setup_roi() and the NVENC qpDeltaMap patch:
+ * regions are iterated in reverse so the *first* region in the list wins on
+ * overlap, each AVRegionOfInterest.qoffset (an AVRational in [-1, +1], negative
+ * asks for lower QP / better quality) is scaled by the codec QP range and
+ * clamped, then written to every 16x16 block its pixel rectangle covers. The
+ * qp_range convention matches libx264 (51 + 6*(bit_depth-8)); MBQP DeltaQP
+ * entries are signed bytes applied on top of the rate-control QP.
+ *
+ * The DeltaQP array itself is the persistent ctx->qp_delta_map (allocated lazily
+ * here, sized from the coded dimensions and reused frame-to-frame). Only the
+ * small mfxExtMBQP header is per-frame; free_encoder_ctrl() reclaims it like the
+ * existing mfxExtEncoderROI path. A frame with no ROI side data attaches nothing,
+ * so the encoder sees a zero delta and behaviour is unchanged. */
+static int qsvenc_setup_roi(AVCodecContext *avctx, const AVFrame *frame,
+                            mfxEncodeCtrl *enc_ctrl)
+{
+    QSVEncContext *q = avctx->priv_data;
+    AVFrameSideData *sd;
+    const AVRegionOfInterest *roi;
+    mfxExtMBQP *mbqp;
+    const AVPixFmtDescriptor *desc;
+    uint32_t roi_size;
+    int nb_rois, mbx, mby, map_size, bit_depth, qp_range;
+    const int blk = PELORUS_QSV_MBQP_BLOCK;
+
+    if (!q->pelorus_roi || !frame)
+        return 0;
+    if (avctx->codec_id != AV_CODEC_ID_HEVC &&
+        avctx->codec_id != AV_CODEC_ID_H264)
+        return 0;
+
+    sd = av_frame_get_side_data(frame, AV_FRAME_DATA_REGIONS_OF_INTEREST);
+    if (!sd)
+        return 0;
+
+    if (enc_ctrl->NumExtParam >= QSV_MAX_ENC_EXTPARAM) {
+        if (!q->roi_warned) {
+            q->roi_warned = 1;
+            av_log(avctx, AV_LOG_WARNING,
+                   "No free mfxEncodeCtrl ext-param slot for the ROI QP map.\n");
+        }
+        return 0;
+    }
+
+    mbx = q->qp_delta_map_w = (avctx->width  + blk - 1) / blk;
+    mby = q->qp_delta_map_h = (avctx->height + blk - 1) / blk;
+    map_size = mbx * mby;
+    if (map_size <= 0)
+        return 0;
+
+    if (!q->qp_delta_map) {
+        q->qp_delta_map = av_calloc(map_size, sizeof(*q->qp_delta_map));
+        if (!q->qp_delta_map)
+            return AVERROR(ENOMEM);
+    }
+
+    desc = av_pix_fmt_desc_get(avctx->sw_pix_fmt == AV_PIX_FMT_NONE ?
+                               avctx->pix_fmt : avctx->sw_pix_fmt);
+    bit_depth = desc ? desc->comp[0].depth : 8;
+    qp_range  = 51 + 6 * (bit_depth - 8);
+
+    roi = (const AVRegionOfInterest *)sd->data;
+    roi_size = roi->self_size;
+    if (!roi_size || sd->size % roi_size) {
+        av_log(avctx, AV_LOG_ERROR, "Invalid AVRegionOfInterest.self_size.\n");
+        return AVERROR(EINVAL);
+    }
+    nb_rois = sd->size / roi_size;
+
+    memset(q->qp_delta_map, 0, map_size);
+
+    /* Reverse iteration: the first region in the list takes precedence on
+     * overlap, so writing it last lets it overwrite later regions. */
+    for (int i = nb_rois - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
+        int startx, endx, starty, endy;
+        float qoffset;
+        int8_t delta;
+
+        roi = (const AVRegionOfInterest *)(sd->data + roi_size * i);
+        if (roi->qoffset.den == 0) {
+            av_log(avctx, AV_LOG_ERROR,
+                   "AVRegionOfInterest.qoffset.den must not be zero.\n");
+            return AVERROR(EINVAL);
+        }
+
+        starty = av_clip(roi->top                / blk, 0, mby);
+        endy   = av_clip((roi->bottom + blk - 1) / blk, 0, mby);
+        startx = av_clip(roi->left               / blk, 0, mbx);
+        endx   = av_clip((roi->right  + blk - 1) / blk, 0, mbx);
+
+        qoffset = roi->qoffset.num * 1.0f / roi->qoffset.den;
+        delta   = av_clip_int8(lrintf(av_clipf(qoffset * qp_range,
+                                               -qp_range, +qp_range)));
+
+        for (int y = starty; y < endy; y++)
+            for (int x = startx; x < endx; x++)
+                q->qp_delta_map[x + y * mbx] = delta;
+    }
+
+    mbqp = av_mallocz(sizeof(*mbqp));
+    if (!mbqp)
+        return AVERROR(ENOMEM);
+    mbqp->Header.BufferId = MFX_EXTBUFF_MBQP;
+    mbqp->Header.BufferSz = sizeof(*mbqp);
+    mbqp->Mode            = MFX_MBQP_MODE_QP_DELTA;
+    mbqp->BlockSize       = blk;   /* honored for HEVC; ignored for AVC */
+    mbqp->Pitch           = mbx;
+    mbqp->NumQPAlloc      = map_size;
+    mbqp->DeltaQP         = q->qp_delta_map;
+
+    enc_ctrl->ExtParam[enc_ctrl->NumExtParam++] = (mfxExtBuffer *)mbqp;
+    return 0;
+}
+#endif
+
 static int set_roi_encode_ctrl(AVCodecContext *avctx, const AVFrame *frame,
                                mfxEncodeCtrl *enc_ctrl)
 {
@@ -2517,7 +2673,20 @@ static int encode_frame(AVCodecContext *avctx, QSVEncContext *q,
         q->set_encode_ctrl_cb(avctx, frame, enc_ctrl);
     }
 
-    if ((avctx->codec_id == AV_CODEC_ID_H264 ||
+#if QSV_HAVE_MBQP
+    /* Pelorus dense per-block QP map (mfxExtMBQP). When pelorus_roi is active it
+     * fully supersedes the coarse mfxExtEncoderROI rectangle path below: the two
+     * are mutually exclusive because attaching both ROI ext-buffers to one
+     * mfxEncodeCtrl is undefined per the oneVPL spec. */
+    if (q->pelorus_roi && enc_ctrl) {
+        ret = qsvenc_setup_roi(avctx, frame, enc_ctrl);
+        if (ret < 0)
+            goto free;
+    }
+#endif
+
+    if (!q->pelorus_roi &&
+        (avctx->codec_id == AV_CODEC_ID_H264 ||
          avctx->codec_id == AV_CODEC_ID_H265) &&
          enc_ctrl && QSV_RUNTIME_VERSION_ATLEAST(q->ver, 1, 8)) {
         ret = set_roi_encode_ctrl(avctx, frame, enc_ctrl);
@@ -2752,6 +2921,10 @@ int ff_qsv_enc_close(AVCodecContext *avctx, QSVEncContext *q)
     av_freep(&q->extparam_str);
     av_freep(&q->extparam);
 
+#if QSV_HAVE_MBQP
+    av_freep(&q->qp_delta_map);
+#endif
+
     return 0;
 }
 
diff --git a/libavcodec/qsvenc.h b/libavcodec/qsvenc.h
index 4bc77f2f7c..b0c4ee4283 100644
--- a/libavcodec/qsvenc.h
+++ b/libavcodec/qsvenc.h
@@ -39,6 +39,13 @@
 #define QSV_HAVE_EXT_VP9_TILES QSV_VERSION_ATLEAST(1, 29)
 #define QSV_HAVE_EXT_AV1_PARAM QSV_VERSION_ATLEAST(2, 5)
 
+/* Pelorus: per-block delta-QP steering via mfxExtMBQP. The buffer, its
+ * MFX_EXTBUFF_MBQP id and mfxExtCodingOption3::EnableMBQP all exist from
+ * MediaSDK / oneVPL API 1.13 onward; gate on it so older SDK headers compile
+ * to a clean no-op (the AVOption then degrades to a one-shot warning). The
+ * MBQP DeltaQP array is documented as 16x16-block-aligned, raster order. */
+#define QSV_HAVE_MBQP  QSV_VERSION_ATLEAST(1, 13)
+
 #if defined(_WIN32) || defined(__CYGWIN__)
 #define QSV_HAVE_AVBR   1
 #define QSV_HAVE_VCM    1
@@ -265,6 +272,17 @@ typedef struct QSVEncContext {
     char *load_plugins;
     SetEncodeCtrlCB *set_encode_ctrl_cb;
     int forced_idr;
+
+    /* Pelorus: per-block QP steering from AV_FRAME_DATA_REGIONS_OF_INTEREST,
+     * gated by the "pelorus_roi" AVOption (default off). When enabled at init
+     * (CQP rate control only) we turn on mfxExtCodingOption3::EnableMBQP and
+     * rasterize each frame's ROI side data into qp_delta_map (one signed byte
+     * per 16x16 block, raster order), carried by a per-frame mfxExtMBQP. */
+    int pelorus_roi;
+    int8_t *qp_delta_map;      ///< persistent per-block delta-QP scratch
+    int     qp_delta_map_w;    ///< blocks across = ceil(width  / 16)
+    int     qp_delta_map_h;    ///< blocks down   = ceil(height / 16)
+    int     roi_warned;        ///< rate-limit incompatibility warnings to once
     int low_delay_brc;
 
     int co2_idx;
diff --git a/libavcodec/qsvenc_h264.c b/libavcodec/qsvenc_h264.c
index 7d39338d6a..a1af783dc1 100644
--- a/libavcodec/qsvenc_h264.c
+++ b/libavcodec/qsvenc_h264.c
@@ -101,6 +101,8 @@ static av_cold int qsv_enc_close(AVCodecContext *avctx)
 #define VE AV_OPT_FLAG_VIDEO_PARAM | AV_OPT_FLAG_ENCODING_PARAM
 static const AVOption options[] = {
     QSV_COMMON_OPTS
+    { "pelorus_roi",  "Honor AV_FRAME_DATA_REGIONS_OF_INTEREST per-region QP via the QSV per-block QP map (CQP only)",
+                                                            OFFSET(qsv.pelorus_roi), AV_OPT_TYPE_BOOL, { .i64 = 0 }, 0, 1, VE },
     QSV_OPTION_RDO
     QSV_OPTION_MAX_FRAME_SIZE
     QSV_OPTION_MAX_SLICE_SIZE
diff --git a/libavcodec/qsvenc_hevc.c b/libavcodec/qsvenc_hevc.c
index ae3981fb72..32855b7001 100644
--- a/libavcodec/qsvenc_hevc.c
+++ b/libavcodec/qsvenc_hevc.c
@@ -305,6 +305,8 @@ static av_cold int qsv_enc_close(AVCodecContext *avctx)
 #define VE AV_OPT_FLAG_VIDEO_PARAM | AV_OPT_FLAG_ENCODING_PARAM
 static const AVOption options[] = {
     QSV_COMMON_OPTS
+    { "pelorus_roi",  "Honor AV_FRAME_DATA_REGIONS_OF_INTEREST per-region QP via the QSV per-block QP map (CQP only)",
+                                                            OFFSET(qsv.pelorus_roi), AV_OPT_TYPE_BOOL, { .i64 = 0 }, 0, 1, VE },
     QSV_OPTION_RDO
     QSV_OPTION_MAX_FRAME_SIZE
     QSV_OPTION_MAX_SLICE_SIZE
